# On any merge conflict under data/ or docs/, always keep OUR (local) version.
#
# Rationale: this repo has two producers of these files — your local pipeline and the
# GitHub Actions runs. Both regenerate the price caches, the rendered site, and the data
# ledgers, so they collide on almost every file every time you pull. Local is the source
# of truth (you run the full pipeline locally), so local always wins; anything CI fetched
# is re-derived on your next run.
#
# This needs the "ours" merge driver defined locally (a no-op that keeps our file) and
# pulls kept as merges (rebase swaps the meaning of ours/theirs):
#   git config merge.ours.driver true
#   git config pull.rebase false
# src/refresh_all.py sets the driver automatically before it pushes. Source code
# (src/, templates/, workflows, config) is intentionally NOT here — those only ever change
# by hand, so a real conflict there should surface, not be silently discarded.

data/**   merge=ours
docs/**   merge=ours
